{"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"title":"Migrating to 1.9"},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.9","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The Composable Architecture is under constant development, and we are always looking for ways to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"simplify the library, and make it more powerful. As such, we often need to deprecate certain APIs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in favor of newer ones. We recommend people update their code as quickly as possible to the newest"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"APIs, and this article contains some tips for doing so."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Sending-test-store-actions","text":"Sending test store actions","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Version 1.4 of the library introduced the ability to receive test store actions using case key path","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"syntax, massively simplifying how one asserts on actions received in a test:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["-store.receive(.child(.presented(.response(.success(\"Hello\")))))","+store.receive(\\.child.response.success)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"While version 1.6 of the library introduced the ability to assert against the payload of a received","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"action:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["store.receive(\\.child.presented.success, \"Hello\")"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.9 introduces similar affordances for "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sending"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" actions to test stores via","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"TestStore\/send(_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)-8877x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestStore\/send(_:_:assert:fileID:file:line:column:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":". These methods can significantly simplify","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"integration-style tests that send deeply-nested actions to child features, and provide symmetry to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"how actions are received:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .destination(.presented(.record(.startButtonTapped))))))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.startButtonTapped)"," store.receive(\\.path[id: 0].destination.record.timerTick)"]},{"name":"Tip","type":"aside","style":"tip","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Case key paths offer specialized syntax for many different action types.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentationAction"},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"presented"},{"type":"text","text":" case can be collapsed:"}]},{"code":["-store.send(.destination(.presented(.tap)))","+store.send(\\.destination.tap)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/IdentifiedAction","type":"reference"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/StackAction","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be subscripted into:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff","code":["-store.send(.path(.element(id: 0, action: .tap)))","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].tap)"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"And ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/BindingAction","isActive":true},{"text":"s can dynamically chain into a key path of state:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["-store.send(.binding(.set(\\.firstName, \"Blob\")))","+store.send(\\.binding.firstName, \"Blob\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"diff"}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Together, these helpers can massively simplify asserting against nested actions:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["-store.send(","-  .path(","-    .element(","-      id: 0,","-      action: .destination(","-        .presented(","-          .sheet(","-            .binding(","-              .set(\\.password, \"blobisawesome\")","-            )","-          )","-        )","-      )","-    )","-  )","-)","+store.send(\\.path[id: 0].destination.sheet.binding.password, \"blobisawesome\")"],"syntax":"diff","type":"codeListing"}]},{"text":"Overriding dependencies","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overriding-dependencies"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Version 1.2 of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"http:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" introduced an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"alternative syntax for referencing a dependency:"}]},{"syntax":"diff","code":["-@Dependency(\\.apiClient) var apiClient","+@Dependency(APIClient.self) var apiClient"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The primary benefit of this syntax is that you do not need to define a dedicated computed property","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on "},{"code":"DependencyValues","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", which saves a small amount of boilerplate.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"There is now a similar API for overriding dependencies on a reducer, "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/dependency(_:)"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"which can be used like so:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["MyFeature()","  .dependency(mockAPIClient)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The type of ","type":"text"},{"code":"mockAPIClient","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" determines how the dependency is overridden.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This style of accessing and overriding dependencies is really only appropriate for dependencies","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"defined directly in your project. If you are shipping a dependency client that is used by others,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then still prefer adding a computed property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DependencyValues"},{"type":"text","text":" in order to be more discoverable."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.9"]}],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","d